questions.explanation: Over the past year, Event Horizon has directly provided over $500,000,000 of voting power (for free) to retail voters across 9 different DAOs. More recently, Event Horizon has greatly expanded the standard of governance UX by launching free AI tooling and voting agents for each voter.

questions.query: What features or use cases does your dApp/App present? How is it differentiated?
questions.explanation:
The original Event Horizon core product served as infrastructure for the creation of publicly shared voting pools. Event Horizon partnered with several DAOs to create pools of voting power and through Event Horizon's voter pass and metagovernance tooling, each retail voter could mint a voter pass (for free) and have one share of rights in how the pool was used to vote in the base DAO proposal. This was all automated and took minutes from start to finish. 

Following this, the Event Horizon team found that the generally accepted standard UX of governance was actually quite taxing on the user. To remediate this, Event Horizon built and launched governance agents. Each user can now create (for free) their own personal voting agent.  These agents learn each user's preferences and personality to automatically vote in their proxy on each and every future proposal. Further, the user may use the agent as an education tool to summarize proposals, learn about the governance process, and even synthesize the perspectives of other delegates through forum and social media discourse.

Event Horizon is the only public access metagovernance solution and the most robust AI governance tool.

questions.query: What are your plans for further development, and how will the grant funds be used to achieve these goals?
questions.explanation: Continuing to expand the models which drive the governance agents as well as the data sourcing is incredibly imperative. Along with this comes notable technical and infrastructural costs. Further, the Event Horizon team would like to continue expanding their marketing efforts to make the availability of these public goods more known.

Describe your previous work or plans related to the Arbitrum ecosystem. How does your project strengthen Arbitrum's foundational infrastructure, improve developer efficiency, or accelerate the adoption of novel applications?
questions.explanation: Event Horizon is the only metagovernance layer on Arbitrum and the broader EVM space. Event Horizon creates community voter pools which allow community members to mint free-to-mint voter passes and begin taking part in community governance. The community pool operates with a 1-pass-1-vote model with additional sybil prevention support provided by Gitcoin Passports.
